    <p>Click the <strong>Add Announcement</strong> button.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="allow-announcement-comments" data-step-uuid="79770a33-eca1-4ce3-a618-ee8c9bcf4a3e">
    <h2 id="allow-announcement-comments" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Allow Comments</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/001/365/880/original/733f9072-6038-4606-ab96-f0df61db7d6a.png" srcset="" alt="Allow Announcement Comments" height="143" width="430">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_a9934513-7bff-42ff-a6e0-9addae80a1b9" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Click the <strong>Allow users to comment</strong> checkbox [1]. You can also require students to reply to a post before seeing other replies [2].</p>
<p>The Allow users to comment option is persistent, meaning the option you select when creating or editing an announcement will carry over when you create a new announcement in the course.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="save-announcement" data-step-uuid="9ce981e9-9d92-49e8-8824-0a58b4f52549">
